    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Lighthouse does already implement the API at v2, you can see the code for that [here](https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/aa72088f8fc91d41106a8afce7a0179cde64ce5d/beacon_node/http_api/src/lib.rs#L1602-L1613).\r\n\r\nHowever, our implementation is currently affected by two bugs which will cause it to return a 405 if a complex `Accept` header is provided, see https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/3114 and https://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/issues/3112. My guess is that your request is setting an accept header that Lighthouse doesn't parse correctly. It would be helpful to see the headers on your HTTP request to confirm this is why it's failing.",
